Stay at home
Only go outside for food, health reasons or work (but only if you cannot work from home)
If you go out, stay 2 metres (6ft) away from other people at all times
Wash your hands as soon as you get home
Do not meet others, even friends or family.
You can spread the virus even if you don’t have symptoms.

Cases of coronavirus (COVID-19) have been confirmed in Bolivia. The authorities have introduced a state of emergency.
For information on returning to the UK from Bolivia, see Return to the UK
International travel
All international flights to and from Bolivia are suspended and all land border crossings closed.
If you’re in Bolivia, you should find secure accommodation until the state of emergency ends, flights resume and borders open. See Return to the UK
Local measures
Movement continues to be restricted nationwide, with quarantine measures extended to 30 April.
One person per household (between the ages of 18 and 65) is allowed to go outside to buy food, once per week between the hours of 7am and 12 midday. The day you can go outside is determined by the final number of your ID card or passport, as follows:
Monday: 1 and 2
Tuesday: 3 and 4
Wednesday: 5 and 6
Thursday: 7 and 8
Friday: 9 and 0
Nobody may go outside on Saturday or Sunday.
No private or public vehicles may circulate, except those related to security and health.
Penalties for breaching these conditions include fines and imprisonment.
Further information
Further information on coronavirus (COVID-19), including advice on preparing for foreign travel and helping reduce the spread of the virus, is available from Public Health England and on the TravelHealthPro website.
